# URL of the Mealie backend.
#
# In development, Vite proxies all /api requests from localhost:3000 to this
# URL. This means:
#   - You do NOT need to configure a separate CORS exception on Mealie
#   - Mealie's OAuth redirect URI (built relative to the incoming request host)
#     will resolve back to http://localhost:3000/login — no extra setup needed
#
# In production this variable is not used at runtime — /api requests are
# handled by your reverse proxy (e.g. nginx, Caddy, Cloudflare) which should
# forward them to Mealie. It is still read at build time by vite.config.ts
# but only affects the dev server proxy.
VITE_MEALIE_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9000
